<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-07-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-07-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="500" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d500">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Russell</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-07-12"><hi rend="italic">July 12,
                                1901.</hi></date></dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 429.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            No. 634, of the 30th ultimo, forwarding the Venezuelan Government’s
                            explanation of the nondelivery of your legation’s telegram of October 24
                            last to the United States consular agent at Barcelona.</p>
                        <p>In reply I have to say that the explanation is satisfactory to this
                            Government.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>